        <documentation>Telkonet EcoInsight, EcoSource Driver.
----------------------------------------------
Version 1.4    May 1, 2013
----------------------------------------------

This driver controls a Zigbee Home Automation Profile Standard Thermostat device.

EcoInsight Joining Procedure
----------------------------------------------
The network status is indicated by 4 bars on the LCD (located just over the wording 'Room Temp').
	No bars - the thermostat is joined to a network
	Two bars - the thermostat is searching for a network to join
	Four bars - the thermostat is not joined to any network.

Press the Cool button 4 times.
If the thermostat is not joined (4 bars on display), the thermostat will search for a network to join for 60 seconds.
If the thermostat is already joined (no bars), it will send an Identify message.

Leaving the network
----------------------------------------------
	1. Hold down the fan button for 10 seconds.
	2. Release the fan button and press the on/off button. This will display the Maintenance menu.
 	3. Press the up arrow (Warm) button and the display will show 'Adv. Prog'. Press On/Off to select.
	4. Press the down arrow (Cool) button and 21 should display beside 'Adv Prog'.
	5. Press On/Off to selct option 21. The thermostat will then leave the network and reboot.

EcoSource Joining Procedure
----------------------------------------------
The EcoSource has a single push button which serves multiple purposes.
The red/green status LED is normally used to indicate connectivity status of the RUI/WOS devices,
and only provides feedback on the ZigBee network during the join process.
	2 red flashes, 1 green flash repeated every 2 seconds - searching for a network to join
	Fast green flashing for 5 seconds - the thermostat has joined a network.
	Red on solid for 5 seconds - the thermostat failed to join a network.

Press the button 5 times.
If the thermostat is not joined, the thermostat will search for a network to join for 60 seconds.
If the thermostat is already joined, it will send an Identify message.


Thermostat Cluster Attributes
----------------------------------------------
	Local Temperature
	Occupied heating setpoint
	Occupied cooling setpoint
	System mode
	Control sequence of operation
	Minimum heat setpoint
	Maximum heat setpoint
	Minimum cool setpoint
	Maximum cool setpoint

Fan Cluster Attributes
----------------------------------------------
	Fan mode
	Fan mode sequence of operation

User Interface Cluster Attributes
----------------------------------------------
	Display mode
	</documentation>
